Ingredients:
 - 3 cups dairy-free milk (coconut, almond, cashew, sesame, etc.)
 - 1/3-1/2 cup natural sweetener (maple syrup, coconut sugar, honey, etc.)
 - Flavouring to taste (vanilla, cinnamon, cacao powder, maca, mint extract,
   etc.)
 - Add-ins of choice (fruit, cacao nibs, nuts or seeds, chocolate chunks, etc.)
 - 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda

Directions:
 1. Put all the ingredients into a bowl and mix well.

 2. Put mixture in the freezer to produce ice cream.
